HEADWORD: Fire-fanged
<hw>Fire"-fanged`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Fire</ets>
+ <ets>fanged</ets> seized.]</ety> <def>Injured as by fire; burned; --
said of manure which has lost its goodness and acquired an ashy hue in
consequence of heat generated by decomposition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

